  "prompt": "Can Home Depot copy a car key with a chip if I provide them a blank key with a chip?",
  "response": "Home Depot typically offers key duplication services for standard keys, but when it comes to car keys with chips (also known as transponder keys), the process is different. They can often duplicate or program car keys with chips, but they usually have to use their own equipment and key blanks specifically designed for that purpose. \n\nIf you bring in a blank key with a chip, they may not be able to duplicate it, as they generally require their own specific types of blanks and programming tools. It's best to contact your local Home Depot or a specialized locksmith for clarification on their capabilities regarding your specific car key, including any costs associated with the duplication and programming services.",
